      • menu

        public int menu()

        Menu

        Description: Displays a general menu and retrieves the user's choice. After displaying the following options, it prompts the user to enter an option and returns it.

        Options:

        1. Register a collaborator
        2. Register a department
        3. Register a request
        4. Change a request's status
          • Allows to create a Knowledge Management Project
          • Allows to create a Transformation and Improvement Project
        5. Close a project
        6. Display the last 5 projects (based on query date) of all the DTI collaborators
          • Allows to access the detailed information of a project
        7. Review efficiency:
          • DTI collaborator
          • Project
          • Request
        8. Consult general information:
          • Projects organized by priority and type
          • Projects led by every DTI team member
          • Number of received and managed requests
        9. Exit Program

        Preconditions:

        • The scanner object sk must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • The user's choice is returned as an integer.
        Returns:
        The user's choice.

      • registerCollaborator

        public void registerCollaborator()

        registerCollaborator

        Description: Registers a collaborator based on the user's input. This method guides the user through the process of registering a collaborator by providing options for the type of collaborator (DTI or general) and collecting relevant information such as full name, ID, email, and extension (optional). It then calls the University.registerCollaborator(int, String, String, String, String) method in the controller class to handle the registration process and returns the message indicating the success or failure of the registration.

        Preconditions:

        • intCollabType must be an int representing the type of collaboratos (1 or 2).
        • The fullName, id, email, and extension parameters must be Strings.
        • The scanner object sk must be initialized.
        • The Controller object controller must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • A collaborator is registered based on the user's input, and a message indicating the success or failure of the registration is returned.

      • registerDepartment

        public void registerDepartment()

        registerDepartment

        Description: Registers a new department in the university system. This method ensures there is at least one saved collaborator in the system before allowing department registration ((University.oneMinCollaborator()). It also checks for the existence of a department with the provided internal code before registering (University.searchDepartment(String)) Then it allows the using to enter the rest of the information. The responsable collaborator must be selected from the list made by University.displayCollaborators(). The method finally calls University.registerDepartment(String, String, String, int) to create the object.

        Preconditions:

        • internalCode must be a String.
        • name must be a String.
        • address must be a String.
        • intResponsibleCollaborator must be an int from the displayed list.

        Postconditions:

        • A new department is registered in the university system.
        • If there wasn't at least one preregistered collaborator, the system will ask the user to enter one.
        • If a department with the provided internal code already exists, an error message is displayed, and the user is prompted to try another internal code.

      • registerRequest

        public void registerRequest()

        registerRequest

        Description: Registers a new request in the system, assigning it to a responsible collaborator and department. The system will first make sure there is at least one registered collaborator (University.oneMinCollaborator()) and one department (University.oneMinDepartment()). Then it will display menus where the user can choose a preregistered collaborator (University.displayCollaborators()) and a department (University.displayDepartments()) Afterwards the use will be able to add the subject of the request and using University.isDuplicateRequest(int, String) will verify whether or not there is another request in the list inside the responsible departement. If there is no duplicate, finally, the user will enter the description.

        Preconditions:

        • controller must be initialized.
        • intResponsibleCollaborator must be an int chosen from the displayed list of collaborators.
        • intResponsibleDepartment must be an int chosen from the displayed list of departments.
        • subject must be a String.
        • description must be a String.

        Postconditions:

        • A new request is registered with the provided subject, description, responsible department, and responsible collaborator.
        • If there is not at least one collaborator registered an "at least one collaborator" message will be printed.
        • If there is not at leaste one department registered an "at least one department" message will be printed.
        • If there is another request with the same subject within the department a "duplicate" message will be printed.

      • changeRequestStatus

        public void changeRequestStatus()

        changeRequestStatus

        Description: Allows changing the status of a pending request within a department. First it checks if there is at least one preregistered department(University.oneMinDepartment()). Second, it checks that at least one of those departments has a pending request (University.oneMinPendingRequest()). Third, it checks there is at leaste one registered leader in case the pending request is accepted (University.oneMinLeader()). If either of does conditions isn't met, the appropiate message is printed. If both filters are passed, then it displays the departments that have at leaste one pending request (University.displayDepartmentsPendingRequest()), where the user can select one from. Then it displays the pending requests inside this department (University.displayPendingRequests(int)) so the user can choose one. Next the system displays the three types of status change the request to (University.displayStatusTypes()) and the user must choose one. Then the system proceeds to change the status with University.changeRequestStatus(int, int, int). If the status is selected, then it will jump to create a project using createProject(int, int).
        See Also:

        Preconditions:

        • {@code departments} array must be initialized.
        • {@code requests} array must be initialized.
        • {@code oneMinDepartment()} and {@code oneMinPendingRequest()} methods should be in place.
        • {@code displayDepartmentsPendingRequest()}, {@code displayPendingRequests(int)}, and {@code displayStatusTypes()} methods should be in place.
        • {@code intRespondableDepartment}, {@code intRequest} and {@code intStatusType} must all be ints within the range of the displayed menus.

        Postconditions:

        • The status of the selected pending request within the department is changed based on the provided status type.
        • If the status type is set to 2 (Approved), a project is created for the corresponding request.
        • If there is not at least one preregistered department it will ask the user to enter one.
        • If there is not at leaste one pending request inside a department, the system will ask the user to enter a request.

      • createProject

        public void createProject(int intResponsibleDepartment,
                          int intRequest)

        createProject

        Description: Creates a new project based on the approved request and user input. This method must be used after a pending request is set to approved changeRequestStatus(). This method starts by asking the type of project (knowledge or improvement) and saves the option. Then, it displays all the possible leaders (only DTI collaborators) using University.displayDtiCollaborators(). Next, displays the possible priorities a project can have (University.displayPriorities()). Afterwards, depending on the selected type of project it will ask for additional information:
        • Knowledge type: A menu displaying the possible impacted communities (University.displayImpactCommunities()) and the types of knowledge projects (University.displayKnowledgeTypes()).
        • Improvement type: The system will ask to enter the processName.
        Finally, the method invokes the methods University.createProject(String, int, int, int, int, String) to create an Improvement project or University.createProject(String, int, int, int, int, int, int) to create a Knowledge project.

        Preconditions:

        • intResponsibleDepartment and intRequest must be valid integers.
        • sk must be initialized to read user input.
        • controller must be initialized to access necessary methods.
        • name and processCode must be Strings.
        • intPriority and intLeader must be integers selected from the displayed menus.

        Postconditions:

        • A Knowledge or an Improvement project is created based on the provided details.
        • The project is assigned a type, name, leader, priority, and other attributes based on user input.
        Parameters:
        intResponsibleDepartment - The index of the responsible department for the project.
        intRequest - The index of the approved request.
